Was debating on posting this. But I hope it helps a person out there that is scared to start over. 
21 & engaged to my best friend. Together 5 years. 
22 & moved to a new city alone. Got a new car. New job. New life.
He hated tattoos, yet I always wanted them. I paid hundreds to keep my hair blonde like he wanted it. I was living to make another person happy.
 I’m proud that the 22 year old girl was able to walk away & live a life for herself. 
Starting over is scary, overwhelming, and sometimes sucks. But once you take that first step, you’ll never want to look back.
Keep the lord in your heart & you’ll have nothing to fear.
